## 📐 Architecture Overview

**ViOS** is a revolutionary operating system that abandons traditional process-based designs in favor of a **Cellular Single Address Space (SAS)** architecture with **Language-Based Isolation (LBI)**.

### System Diagram

```mermaid
graph TD
    subgraph "User Space - Cells"
        A[Applications]
        S[Services]
        D[Drivers]
    end

    subgraph "Kernel Space"
        K[Nano Kernel]
        L[Runtime Linker]
        M[Memory Manager]
        T[Task Scheduler]
    end

    subgraph "Hardware Abstraction"
        HAL[HAL Core]
        RV[RISC-V]
        ARM[ARM]
        X86[x86]
    end

    A --> K
    S --> K
    D --> K
    K --> L
    K --> M
    K --> T
    K --> HAL
    HAL --> RV
    HAL --> ARM
    HAL --> X86
```

